Referring to the diagram above, to find an approximate solution to this
problem, we first set the initial conditions

\begin{align*}
u_n^0 = 0 \;\; \text{for} \;\;  n = 0, 1, 2, \cdots, N
\end{align*} and the
boundary condition

\begin{align*}
u_N^k = 0 \;\; \text{for}  \;\; k = 1, 2, 3, \cdots
\end{align*} Then, we compute
$u_n^1$ from $u_n^0$ by

\begin{align*}
u_0^1 =  u_0^0 + \frac{\Delta t}{(\Delta x)^2}[u_{1}^0 - u_0^0] + t_0 \Delta t
\end{align*}
and

\begin{align*}
u_n^{1} = u_n^0 + \frac{\Delta t}{(\Delta x)^2}[u_{n+1}^0 - 2 u_n^0 + u_{n-1}^0] + t_0 \Delta t \;\; \text{for} \;\; n = 1, 2, 3, \cdots, N.
\end{align*}
Once we have $u_n^1$, we can iterate the process to find
$u_n^2, u_n^3, \cdots$
